title: Definitions
context: [Part II.] PEER REVIEW PROCESS [ยง466-31] Definitions. As used in this part, unless the context clearly indicates otherwise: &ldquo;Rating&rdquo; means the type of report issued following a peer review. Rating shall be &ldquo;pass&rdquo;, &ldquo;pass with deficiency&rdquo;, or &ldquo;fail&rdquo;. &ldquo;Sponsoring organization&rdquo; means a third-party entity that meets the standards specified by this part for administering a peer review.
